    "Specifically, the Monte Carlo simulation employs the following Euler-Maruyama discretization scheme:X (i) t+∆t = X (i) t + κ(η -X (i) t)∆t + σξ t + N∆t k=1 J k, i = 1,...,N, where ξ t ∼ N 0,∆t, N ∆t ∼ Po(Λ∆t) is a Poisson random variable with rate Λ∆t, and J k 's are i.i.d.",
    "random variables for jump sizes distributed as N m,v 2.Figure 2 illustrates the TV distance between P MC and P S. The TV distance remains consistently on the order of 10 -2, which demonstrates the relative accuracy of our method across time.",
